A term related to the cooperation of local communities, see [[Global Villages]] and [[Global Villages Network]]

The term surfaced on 4th of July 2010 in a meeting in Vienna. Les Squires introduced the "G2G concept" as "Group to Group" and Franz Nahrada answered "Then we could also call it "Village to Village"

Village2Village - V2V is a special form of P2P.

